  "reasoning": "The azx_init_chip() function at line 1209 has a bug where it doesn't reset chip->polling_mode to 0 during full reset. When a codec timeout occurs before suspend, polling_mode is set to 1. During suspend, azx_stop_chip() is called which sets chip->initialized=0 but does NOT reset polling_mode. During resume, azx_init_chip() is called with full_reset=1, but it fails to reset polling_mode back to 0. This causes subsequent codec communication attempts to fail with timeouts because the chip remains in an error state. The fix requires adding 'chip->polling_mode = 0;' at the beginning of azx_init_chip() or checking/resetting it when full_reset is true."
}

